sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as JavaScript trading app
    participant CCXT as CCXT gmx exchange
    participant Bridge as API bridge
    participant PyGMX as Python GMX exchange
    participant Trader as GMXTrading
    participant Wallet as Signing wallet
    participant RPC as Arbitrum RPC
    participant GMX as GMX contracts on Arbitrum
    participant Indexer as Subsquid / EventEmitter

    App->>CCXT: import ccxt, new ccxt.gmx(...)\ncreateOrder(symbol, "market", "buy", amount, params)
    CCXT->>Bridge: POST /call\nmethod=create_order
    Bridge->>PyGMX: BridgeRuntime.call("create_order", ...)
    PyGMX->>PyGMX: load markets, normalise params,\nensure approvals if needed
    PyGMX->>Trader: open_position(...)
    Trader-->>PyGMX: OrderResult with unsigned tx
    PyGMX->>Wallet: sign_transaction_with_new_nonce(tx)
    Wallet-->>PyGMX: signed transaction
    PyGMX->>RPC: eth_sendRawTransaction
    RPC->>GMX: broadcast createOrder tx
    GMX-->>RPC: tx hash
    RPC-->>PyGMX: tx hash
    PyGMX->>RPC: wait_for_transaction_receipt(tx_hash)
    RPC-->>PyGMX: transaction receipt
    PyGMX->>PyGMX: extract_order_key_from_receipt()

    alt Order executed in the same transaction
        PyGMX->>PyGMX: extract_order_execution_result()\nmark order closed
    else Keeper executes after creation tx
        PyGMX->>Indexer: get trade action by order key
        alt Indexed execution found
            Indexer-->>PyGMX: OrderExecuted / execution price / size
        else Fallback to direct log scan
            PyGMX->>RPC: scan GMX EventEmitter logs
            RPC-->>PyGMX: execution or cancellation event
        end
        PyGMX->>PyGMX: confirm execution or raise keeper error
    end

    PyGMX-->>Bridge: CCXT order result\nstatus=closed when trade is confirmed
    Bridge-->>CCXT: JSON response
    CCXT-->>App: resolved order / trade confirmed
